Name: patterned macular dystrophy 2
Definition: A patterned macular dystrophy characterized by bilateral accumulation of pigmented or yellowish material at the level of the retinal pigment epithelium in lesions that resemble the wings of a butterfly that has material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the CTNNA1 gene on chromosome 5q31.

Name: patterned macular dystrophy 3
Definition: A patterned macular dystrophy characterized by a 'dry desert land' pattern of the fundus

Name: patterned macular dystrophy 1
Definition: A patterned macular dystrophy characterized by bilateral accumulation of pigmented or yellowish material at the level of the retinal pigment epithelium in lesions that resemble the wings of a butterfly that has material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the PRPH2 gene on chromosome 6p21.
